# Internationalization

- **All** user-facing strings go through react-i18next — no hardcoded English in components
- Init: `src/shared/lib/i18n.ts`; supported locales: `en`, `ml`
- Use `useTranslation('<namespace>')` with the feature namespace

## Namespaces

- One JSON file per feature matching folder name exactly: `booking-management.json`, `audit-logs.json`, etc.
- Shared strings: `common.json`
- Files live in both `src/locales/en/` and `src/locales/ml/`

## Adding keys

- **Always** add new keys to **both** `en/` and `ml/` files simultaneously
- `ml/` value may be empty string or `TODO` placeholder initially — never skip the file
- Key naming: nested by context — `list.title`, `form.submit`, `errors.required`

## Example

```tsx
const { t } = useTranslation('booking-management');
return <h1>{t('list.title')}</h1>;
```
